Citation.sAbstract: Experimental data for the isothermal (vapour + liquid) equilibrium of mixtures formed by several cyclic  ethers (tetrahydrofuran, tetrahydropyran, 1,3-dioxolane, and 1,4-dioxane) and chlorohexane at temperatures  of (298.15 and 328.15) K are presented. Experimental results have been discussed in terms of both,  molecular characteristics of pure compounds and potential intermolecular interaction between them  using thermodynamic information of the mixtures obtained earlier. Furthermore, the influence of the  temperature on the (vapour + liquid) equilibrium of these mixtures has been explored and discussed.  Transferable parameters of the SAFT-VR approach together with standard combining rules have been  used to model the phase equilibrium of the mixtures and a description of the (vapour + liquid) equilibrium  of them that is in excellent agreement with the experimental data are provided.
Citation.sTitle: Isothermal (vapour + liquid) equilibrium of (cyclic ethers + chlorohexane) mixtures: Experimental results and SAFT modelling
